  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance capacity of flood affected women-headed households for lifesaving economic/livelihood restor</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Where does the income come from?
UN Women - BDT 49,764,048
- What is the purpose of the package?
To address urgent lifesaving needs of female headed hoodhoods (most at risk), living in emergency shelters, with emergency conditional and unrestricted cash grant to initiate a livelihood followed by livelihoods training, that saves their dignity and ultimately the lives. 
- Where is the money to be allocated? For how long?
Commence 12 Nov 2019 and will terminate on 29 Feb 2020.</narrative>
  </description>
